# =====================================================
# HOSTINGER-SPECIFIC SETTINGS
# =====================================================

# Hostinger Database Credentials
# Get these from: Hostinger Dashboard > Databases > MySQL Databases
# DB_HOST is usually 'localhost' on shared hosting
# DB_USER format: u123456789_dbuser
# DB_NAME format: u123456789_adilgfx

# Hostinger File Paths
# Absolute path to public_html: /home/u123456789/public_html
# Backend directory: /home/u123456789/public_html/backend
# Uploads directory: /home/u123456789/public_html/backend/uploads
# Cache directory: /home/u123456789/public_html/backend/cache

# Hostinger SMTP Settings
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.hostinger.com
# SMTP_PORT=587 (for TLS) or 465 (for SSL)
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@adilgfx.com
# SMTP_ENCRYPTION=tls or ssl

# =====================================================
# SECURITY CHECKLIST
# =====================================================
# ✓ Change JWT_SECRET to a strong random value
# ✓ Use strong database passwords (20+ chars)
# ✓ Use strong email passwords
# ✓ Keep this .env file secure (never commit to git)
# ✓ Set file permissions: chmod 600 .env
# ✓ Regularly rotate JWT_SECRET and passwords
# ✓ Enable HTTPS (SSL certificate) on Hostinger
# ✓ Set APP_ENV=production in production
# ✓ Set APP_DEBUG=false in production
# ✓ Set VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=false in production

# =====================================================
# QUICK START COMMANDS
# =====================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env with your actual values: nano .env
# 3. Set secure permissions: chmod 600 .env
# 4. Test database connection: php backend/config/database.php
# 5. Import database schema: mysql -u user -p database < backend/database/schema.sql
# 6. Run data import: php backend/scripts/install_database.php
# 7. Create directories: mkdir -p backend/cache backend/uploads
# 8. Set permissions: chmod 777 backend/cache backend/uploads
# 9. Build frontend: npm run build
# 10. Deploy to Hostinger file manager or FTP

# =====================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =====================================================
# If you encounter issues:
# - Verify database credentials are correct
# - Check Hostinger PHP version is 7.4+
# - Ensure all required PHP extensions are enabled
# - Check file permissions (755 for directories, 644 for files)
# - Verify .htaccess is configured correctly
# - Check error logs: /home/username/logs/
# - Test API endpoint: curl https://adilgfx.com/backend/api/auth/verify
